\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::2><!$Scr_Ps::1><$Scr_Ps::0>
\f2\b\fs32 Compound Gauge
\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\fs32 :  These gauges can measure both positive and negative (vacuum) pressures, making them suitable for applications where both types of pressure need to be monitored. There is no distinct zero point on these gauges because it moves as the atmospheric pressure changes.  The pressure and vacuum scales are usually marked with different units.  On the gauge shown, positive pressures are in psi or bar, and vacuums are in inches mercury, and bars absolute.\
\pard\sb40\sa40\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

